    <node id="Eastern Mediterranean Region">
      <data key="d0">Eastern Mediterranean Region</data>
      <data key="d1">location</data>
      <data key="d2">The Eastern Mediterranean Region refers to a geographical area experiencing a significant increase in diabetes mellitus cases, making it a public health concern.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is a geographical area where diabetes and impaired glucose tolerance (IGT) prevalence rates are among the highest worldwide.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is a geographical area consisting of several countries with diverse populations and a significant prevalence of diabetes mellitus.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is mentioned as a location where type 2 diabetes should be screened in children.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is noted for a rising prevalence of type 2 diabetes, prompting increased awareness and screening initiatives.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is noted for a rising prevalence of type 2 diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is identified as having a high prevalence of diabetic nephropathy, being a significant cause of renal failure and premature death among diabetic patients.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d8c827cc2249067692290d6a8a0e8018&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f15f59b3ff05825a61f252ed8f9a74e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1400e1158e4f7be2283a0366ebf4f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25fb88c8ed14936954356d104de095d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5384df975133ef2a52113cd3ca0f897e</data>
