    <node id="IGT">
      <data key="d0">IGT</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">IGT (Impaired Glucose Tolerance) is a condition characterized by abnormal glucose regulation, a risk factor for developing diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Impaired Glucose Tolerance (IGT) is a prediabetic state where blood glucose levels are higher than normal but not yet high enough to be classified as diabetes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894215</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="IFG">
      <data key="d0">IFG</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">IFG (Impaired Fasting Glycemia) is defined by specific blood glucose concentration levels and is considered a risk category for diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Impaired Fasting Glucose (IFG) is a metabolic condition that increases the risk of developing type 2 diabetes and cardiovascular diseases due to elevated fasting blood glucose levels.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894216</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Da Quing Study">
      <data key="d0">Da Quing Study</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">The Da Quing Study is a research study conducted in China that demonstrated the effectiveness of diet and exercise in reducing the risk of diabetes mellitus in patients with IGT.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894216</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tuomilehto Study">
      <data key="d0">Tuomilehto Study</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">The Tuomilehto Study is a clinical trial in Finland that showed a significant reduction in the incidence of type 2 diabetes through lifestyle intervention among individuals with IGT.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894216</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Diabetes Prevention Programme Research Group">
      <data key="d0">Diabetes Prevention Programme Research Group</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The Diabetes Prevention Programme Research Group is a collective involved in a study assessing the impact of lifestyle changes and metformin on preventing type 2 diabetes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894216</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Community-Based Healthy Lifestyle Programme">
      <data key="d0">Community-Based Healthy Lifestyle Programme</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A community-based healthy lifestyle programme focuses on promoting healthy weight and physical activity among populations to prevent type 2 diabetes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894216</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Diabetes Mellitus">
      <data key="d0">Diabetes Mellitus</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Diabetes Mellitus is a common noncommunicable disease characterized primarily by high blood sugar levels, leading to an array of related complications. It is recognized as a serious chronic disease increasingly prevalent in regions such as the Eastern Mediterranean. This metabolic disorder results from issues with insulin, whether due to deficiency or ineffectiveness, and can manifest in various forms including type 1 and type 2 diabetes.

The condition is defined by chronic hyperglycemia, which affects the metabolism of carbohydrates, fats, and proteins. Over time, sustained high blood glucose levels can lead to significant health complications, such as retinopathy, neuropathy, nephropathy, and dyslipidaemia, which affects cholesterol and triglyceride levels. Management of Diabetes Mellitus is crucial and typically requires monitoring of blood sugar levels, along with lifestyle adjustments and specific medical interventions to prevent severe complications like ketoacidosis and hypoglycemia.

Diabetes Mellitus encompasses a group of related disorders that hinder the body's ability to utilize blood sugar effectively. This underlying dysfunction not only heightens the risk for other metabolic complications but also necessitates ongoing management strategies to control blood glucose levels and mitigate health risks.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56d9ff3515afac60e7566e41837249a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0748670b42b0f4e0b2ed9c5ce62d54e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8c827cc2249067692290d6a8a0e8018&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85ef35aaa38ac4f0c032c8bc3f6df559&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b253411e54c35aa95f5f9179723bba3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ef79f22f40772c2060b439008ce485b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5fc5e661d0f94cc23c0188b9bbe4e08&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f15f59b3ff05825a61f252ed8f9a74e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1400e1158e4f7be2283a0366ebf4f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd4cfbed43aa26af0eef694fecac2177&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5384df975133ef2a52113cd3ca0f897e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25fb88c8ed14936954356d104de095d4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894216</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="United Kingdom Prospective Diabetes Study">
      <data key="d0">United Kingdom Prospective Diabetes Study</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">The United Kingdom Prospective Diabetes Study is a major research study providing evidence about diabetes management and outcomes.&lt;SEP&gt;The United Kingdom Prospective Diabetes Study demonstrated that good glucose and blood pressure control can significantly reduce complications related to diabetes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894216</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Diabetes Control and Complications Trial">
      <data key="d0">Diabetes Control and Complications Trial</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">The Diabetes Control and Complications Trial is a significant study that examines the long-term effects of diabetes management on complications.&lt;SEP&gt;The Diabetes Control and Complications Trial is a research study in the USA that established the importance of blood glucose control in preventing complications of type 1 diabetes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894216</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Laser Photocoagulation">
      <data key="d0">Laser Photocoagulation</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Laser photocoagulation is a medical treatment used to address retinopathy and prevent vision loss in individuals with diabetes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894216</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Diabetes mellitus">
      <data key="d0">Diabetes mellitus</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Diabetes mellitus refers to a group of diseases that affect how the body uses blood sugar (glucose), which can lead to severe complications if not managed properly.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894216</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Type 2 Diabetes">
      <data key="d0">Type 2 Diabetes</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Type 2 diabetes is a chronic condition characterized by insulin resistance and high blood glucose levels, often leading to serious health complications.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 diabetes is a more common form of diabetes typically characterized by insulin resistance and a higher risk of developing hyperglycemic hyperosmolar states.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894217</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Dyslipidaemia">
      <data key="d0">Dyslipidaemia</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Dyslipidaemia refers to abnormal lipid levels in the blood, often associated with increased cardiovascular disease risk.&lt;SEP&gt;Dyslipidaemia is a medical condition characterized by abnormal lipid levels in the blood, necessitating the investigation of secondary causes.&lt;SEP&gt;Dyslipidaemia is a disorder of lipid metabolism that can complicate type 2 diabetes and lead to cardiovascular disease.&lt;SEP&gt;Dyslipidaemia refers to abnormal lipid levels in the blood, which can be a risk factor in patients with diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Dyslipidaemia refers to abnormal amounts of lipids in the blood, often associated with diabetes and other health issues.&lt;SEP&gt;Dyslipidaemia refers to an abnormal amount of lipids in the blood, often managed through lifestyle changes and medication.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894217</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cardiovascular Disease">
      <data key="d0">Cardiovascular Disease</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Cardiovascular disease refers to a range of heart and blood vessel disorders that can be prevented through effective management of type 2 diabetes and related conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;Cardiovascular disease encompasses a range of heart and blood vessel disorders, for which aspirin therapy is used as preventive treatment.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894217</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Screening for Type 2 Diabetes">
      <data key="d0">Screening for Type 2 Diabetes</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Screening for type 2 diabetes involves testing asymptomatic adults, especially those with high-risk factors, to allow for early detection and intervention.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894217</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Individuals with Type 2 Diabetes">
      <data key="d0">Individuals with Type 2 Diabetes</data>
      <data key="d1">group</data>
      <data key="d2">Individuals diagnosed with type 2 diabetes often experience various complications, including microvascular and macrovascular issues.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894217</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Oral Anti-Hyperglycaemic Agents">
      <data key="d0">Oral Anti-Hyperglycaemic Agents</data>
      <data key="d1">medication</data>
      <data key="d2">Oral anti-hyperglycaemic agents are medications prescribed to manage blood glucose levels in patients with type 2 diabetes when lifestyle changes are insufficient.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894217</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Insulin Therapy">
      <data key="d0">Insulin Therapy</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Insulin therapy is a treatment necessary to control hyperglycaemia in patients with type 1 diabetes, and sometimes used for type 2 diabetes in more severe cases.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894217</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Gestational Diabetes Mellitus">
      <data key="d0">Gestational Diabetes Mellitus</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Gestational diabetes mellitus is a form of diabetes that occurs during pregnancy and can lead to complications for both mothers and babies.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894217</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="First-Degree Relative with Type 2 Diabetes">
      <data key="d0">First-Degree Relative with Type 2 Diabetes</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Having a first-degree relative with type 2 diabetes is considered a high-risk characteristic that increases an individual's likelihood of developing the disease.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894218</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Ethnicity Risk Factors">
      <data key="d0">Ethnicity Risk Factors</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Certain ethnicities, including Pacific Islanders, Australian Aborigines, Mauritian, migrant Asian Indians, Chinese, Indigenous Americans, and Arabs, show increased prevalence and risk for type 2 diabetes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894218</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hypertension Management Protocol">
      <data key="d0">Hypertension Management Protocol</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Hypertension Management Protocol outlines gradual methods to lower blood pressure and avoid complications in patients, particularly the elderly.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8361af576f7e73b0bd2ea813976f60b3</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894218</data>
