    <node id="LDL Cholesterol">
      <data key="d0">LDL Cholesterol</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">LDL cholesterol is a type of cholesterol that, when elevated, increases the risk of cardiovascular disease.&lt;SEP&gt;LDL cholesterol is a primary target in dyslipidaemia management, with a recommended level of less than 100 mg/dL for certain patient groups.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8361af576f7e73b0bd2ea813976f60b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894218</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Triglycerides">
      <data key="d0">Triglycerides</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Triglycerides are a type of fat found in the blood, and elevated levels can contribute to cardiovascular disease risk.&lt;SEP&gt;Triglycerides are a type of fat in the blood, with management goals varying based on levels; critical thresholds for intervention are ≥500 mg/dL and ≥200 mg/dL.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8361af576f7e73b0bd2ea813976f60b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894218</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Coronary Heart Disease">
      <data key="d0">Coronary Heart Disease</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Coronary Heart Disease is a condition that affects blood flow to the heart, where management is influenced by cholesterol levels, particularly LDL.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8361af576f7e73b0bd2ea813976f60b3</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894218</data>
