    <node id="World Health Organization">
      <data key="d0">World Health Organization</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The World Health Organization is an international public health agency responsible for coordinating health efforts and informing global health policy.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization (WHO) is a specialized agency of the United Nations responsible for international public health efforts, including initiatives for chronic diseases like diabetes mellitus.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization provides criteria for diagnosing diabetes mellitus and conditions related to gestational diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization is a specialized agency of the United Nations focused on international public health.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization is a specialized agency of the United Nations concerned with international public health and has organized meetings on diabetes.</data>
