    </node>
    <node id="Type 1 Diabetes Mellitus">
      <data key="d0">Type 1 Diabetes Mellitus</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Type 1 Diabetes Mellitus requires insulin for survival, primarily due to autoimmune destruction of pancreatic beta cells.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 1 diabetes mellitus is an autoimmune condition resulting from the destruction of insulin-producing beta cells.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 1 Diabetes Mellitus is a form of diabetes primarily diagnosed through specific tests like HLA typing and immunological markers.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 1 Diabetes Mellitus is a form of diabetes that requires regular eye examinations soon after diagnosis.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ef79f22f40772c2060b439008ce485b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25fb88c8ed14936954356d104de095d4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894221</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Ketoacidosis">
      <data key="d0">Ketoacidosis</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Ketoacidosis is a serious complication of diabetes, characterized by high levels of ketones due to insulin deficiency.&lt;SEP&gt;Ketoacidosis is a serious acute complication of diabetes, primarily affecting individuals with type 1 diabetes, and is characterized by the build-up of ketones in the blood.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894221</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Obesity">
      <data key="d0">Obesity</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Obesity is a significant risk factor associated with type 2 diabetes and can exacerbate insulin resistance.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity is a metabolic disorder characterized by excess body fat, contributing to cardiovascular risk factors.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity is a significant risk factor for diabetes and its complications, emphasizing the need for weight management in patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity is characterized by excessive body fat, contributing to insulin resistance and related health risks.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity is identified as a global epidemic that impacts public health and diabetes prevalence.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-942e000d0de99e8628ab9c8bcbe83419&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
