    <node id="Diabetes">
      <data key="d0">Diabetes</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Diabetes, specifically diabetes mellitus, refers to a group of diseases that affect how the body uses blood sugar (glucose), often related to metabolic syndrome and having high prevalence in individuals with hypertension.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetes is a chronic condition that affects metabolic processes, particularly glucose regulation in the body.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetes is a chronic condition associated with high blood sugar levels that can lead to various complications, including infections and atherosclerosis.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetes is a chronic condition that leads to various complications, including neuropathy and lower-limb amputations.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetes refers to a chronic health condition characterized by high blood sugar levels and associated complications that require management and prevention strategies.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2173942c84747feba52cff952903a7f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55d2691a8c714949752d249721fec5e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
