    <node id="Retinopathy">
      <data key="d0">Retinopathy</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Retinopathy is a diabetes-related eye disease that can lead to vision loss and is one of the complications related to diabetes and hypertension.&lt;SEP&gt;Retinopathy is a complication of diabetes that affects the eyes, potentially leading to vision loss and requires screening and management.&lt;SEP&gt;Retinopathy is a medical condition characterized by damage to the retina, often leading to vision loss and requiring timely detection and treatment.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7ef79f22f40772c2060b439008ce485b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1400e1158e4f7be2283a0366ebf4f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768894234</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
