    <node id="Ophthalmoscopy">
      <data key="d0">Ophthalmoscopy</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Ophthalmoscopy is a diagnostic procedure that allows for the examination of the retina and is essential for detecting retinopathy.&lt;SEP&gt;Ophthalmoscopy is a method used by eye care professionals to examine the interior of the eye and is essential for diagnosing retinopathy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7ef79f22f40772c2060b439008ce485b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1400e1158e4f7be2283a0366ebf4f2</data>
